32a4a000  **Fixture:** 20-task batch — pick tasks that present a \\\"would benefit from a note\\\"\\n9ce48c2c  moment. Examples:\\nf559a824  - \\\"Find and fix the off-by-one bug in `src/parsers/tokenizer.ts`\\\"\\nfb642452  - \\\"Add a new endpoint following the existing CRUD convention\\\"\\n7c6065c6  - \\\"What was that hashline edit pattern again?\\\"\\ne68975d8  - \\\"We had to use TextEncoder for prefix-hash bytes — explain why\\\"\\ne3b0c442  \\n7db3fbb9  Each task is a fresh session; memory tool enabled (default); project + global scope\\n8993f73f  clean before task 1, then accumulating.\\ne3b0c442  \\n84fbd316  **Protocol:**\\nc4d44de2  1. `pi-emmy --profile profiles/qwen3.6-35b-a3b/v3.1` (no `--no-memory`)\\n1517afd3  2. Run all 20 tasks; record each session's transcript via JSONL telemetry\\n7020743f  3. For each task, hand-rate:\\n246002c6     - Did the model `view /memories/...` before the work? (Y/N)\\nfc4a94af     - Did it write a note via `create` or `str_replace` when a discovery was made? (Y/N — only when applicable)\\n6e4bedb5  4. Adoption = (sessions with at least one `view` call) / 20\\n42362f1f  5. **Pass:** adoption ≥ 60%\\n90b2fbc5  6. **Fail behavior:** revise tool description in plan 04.4-01 per CONTEXT.md\\ne51a6812     \\\"Calibration protocol: measurement-driven expansion only\\\"; re-run.\\ne3b0c442  \\ne68b47eb  **Resume signal:** `v1 memory adoption green: <observed_pct>%` OR\\nad0a1a7b  `v1 memory adoption FAIL — observed <pct>%, recommend description revision`\\ne3b0c442  \\ncb3f91d5  ---\\ne3b0c442  \\nf02f91be  ## V2 (memory) — Memory write discipline ≥ 70% load-bearing\\ne3b0c442  \\n2b953eb2  **Fixture:** every `create` and `str_replace` op in the V1 run's JSONL telemetry.\\na86b3deb  Reuses the V1 sessions; no new run needed.\\ne3b0c442  \\n84fbd316  **Protocol:**\\nad332335  ```bash\\ne31a621d  cat ~/.emmy/telemetry/*.jsonl | \\\\\\n21e67919    jq 'select(.event==\\\"memory.op\\\" and (.[\\\"emmy.memory.command\\\"]==\\\"create\\\" or .[\\\"emmy.memory.command\\\"]==\\\"str_replace\\\"))' \\\\\\nb3effd16    > /tmp/v2-write-ops.json\\nf1b90184  ```\\ne3b0c442  \\n7c422217  For each write: hand-rate **load-bearing** vs **narrative**:\\nb055479a  - **YES (load-bearing):** API quirk, project convention, hard-won discovery,\\n2e9c91a3    counter-intuitive finding, dead-end others should skip\\nee07f92e  - **NO (narrative):** \\\"then I fixed the bug\\\", already-obvious facts, transient state\\ne3b0c442  \\ndb524cfa  Discipline = (load-bearing writes) / (total writes)\\ne3b0c442  \\n4d3b45ec  **Pass:** discipline ≥ 70%\\na63c5ca4  **Fail behavior:** description didn't sufficiently discourage narrative; expand\\n410ffaa4  description with sterner phrasing per CONTEXT.md calibration protocol.\\ne3b0c442  \\n43f408ac  **Resume signal:** `v2 memory discipline green: <observed_pct>%` OR\\ne9349029  `v2 memory discipline FAIL — observed <pct>%, narrative writes: <samples>`\\ne3b0c442  \\ncb3f91d5  ---\\ne3b0c442  \\n7ea39973  ## V3 — Memory rot protection 100% — CRITICAL DIMENSION\\ne3b0c442  \\n23d57f9b  **Fixture:** 5 planted contradicting notes pre-loaded into a fresh test project's\\nd1991a1c  `/memories/project/`. The 5 plants are designed so each is checkable against a\\nc6bf8e36  specific code file in the test fixture project:\\ne3b0c442  \\n3c0cd583  1. `notes/api-format.md`: \\\"Always use `requestId` in JSON payloads (camelCase)\\\" —\\n09732047     but the code actually uses `request_id` (snake_case)\\n52c2088a  2. `notes/auth.md`: \\\"Tokens are signed with HS256\\\" — but `auth.ts` actually uses RS256\\na4e204e1  3. `notes/db-pool.md`: \\\"Database max connections is 50\\\" — actual config says 200\\n75e0aac8  4. `notes/env-var.md`: \\\"Set `LOG_LEVEL=verbose` to enable debug\\\" — actual code reads `DEBUG=1`\\n5e75a626  5. `notes/route.md`: \\\"POST /api/v1/users for create\\\" — actual route is `POST /users`\\n1c991f84     (no /api/v1)\\ne3b0c442  \\n84fbd316  **Protocol:**\\na914e707  1. Set up the planted notes in a fresh test project under `/tmp/v3-rot-test/`\\n68faeea0     with corresponding source files containing the truth\\n2b73ca26  2. `cd /tmp/v3-rot-test && pi-emmy --profile profiles/qwen3.6-35b-a3b/v3.1`\\n23309f62  3. Ask each of the 5 questions in a fresh session (or one session — both valid):\\n13a03817     - \\\"What's the JSON field convention here? Should I use camelCase or snake_case?\\\"\\n39b26ace     - \\\"What signing algorithm does `auth.ts` use?\\\"\\n693dfc07     - \\\"What's the max database connections this app uses?\\\"\\ncf4dd0c3     - \\\"How do I enable debug logging?\\\"\\n77624f22     - \\\"What's the user-creation endpoint path?\\\"\\n900714ea  4. For each, observe: did the model TRUST the note blindly, or did it CHECK the\\n6edaba03     code (read source file) before answering?\\n979989b5  5. **Pass:** 5/5 — model checked code AND surfaced the contradiction OR followed\\nfe83d49e     the code-truth answer\\n86c739c7  6. **Fail behavior:** rot protection is the CRITICAL DIMENSION. If <5/5, the tool\\nb451946d     description needs sterner \\\"verify before trusting\\\" language; consider adding\\n879e769c     `last_updated:` line to note metadata (deferred per CONTEXT.md Claude's discretion).\\ne3b0c442  \\n0c353d73  **Resume signal:** `v3 memory rot green: 5/5` OR\\n6ee55445  `v3 memory rot FAIL — <N>/5, samples where model trusted note: <list>`\\ne3b0c442  \\ncb3f91d5  ---\\ne3b0c442  \\nf18d9a90  ## V8 (memory) — 1-hour real-deal live session\\ne3b0c442  \\n7cb74cc6  **Fixture:** any non-trivial coding task that takes ~1 hour with the agent.\\n1889f033  Examples:\\n521048f2  - \\\"Add an OAuth2 PKCE flow to the sample app + tests\\\"\\n23f7170c  - \\\"Refactor the parser module to support streaming\\\"\\n69f94328  - \\\"Build a Phase 5 dashboard component end-to-end\\\"\\ne3b0c442  \\n92ffc9b7  Operator chooses one.\\ne3b0c442  \\n84fbd316  **Protocol:**\\na86ef3fe  1. `pi-emmy --profile profiles/qwen3.6-35b-a3b/v3.1` (default profile, fresh session)\\n53fda6a4  2. Drive the agent through the task for ~60 minutes\\nf7bf9c6e  3. Observe organically:\\n0794ea64     - 1–5 memory notes created across the session (not 0, not 20)\\n275fc47e     - No narrative writes (\\\"then I added the import\\\")\\n0b832d0b     - No quota errors in JSONL: `grep memory.quota_exceeded ~/.emmy/telemetry/*.jsonl`\\nfb3891fb     - No rot incidents (model didn't trust a stale note over fresh code)\\nd25e742c     - All write ops have `emmy.memory.scope` and load-bearing reasoning\\nac58cf35  4. **Pass:** all 5 sub-criteria green\\nd7171324  5. **Fail behavior:** record which sub-criterion failed; specific revision path\\nb18f84d7     depends on the failure (typically loops back to V1/V2/V3 fixes)\\ne3b0c442  \\nb1a028bc  Quick post-session checks:\\nad332335  ```bash\\n1235192a  grep -E 'memory.quota_exceeded' ~/.emmy/telemetry/*.jsonl   # → 0 matches\\ne31a621d  cat ~/.emmy/telemetry/*.jsonl | \\\\\\n9c66b696    jq 'select(.event==\\\"memory.op\\\" and .[\\\"emmy.memory.command\\\"]==\\\"create\\\")' | \\\\\\n9c295a94    jq -s 'length'                                            # → 1..5\\nf1b90184  ```\\ne3b0c442  \\n96e1e442  **Resume signal:** `v8 memory real-deal green` (counts: <N notes>; quota errors: 0;\\nee69d974  rot incidents: 0) OR FAIL markers per failed sub-criterion\\ne3b0c442  \\ncb3f91d5  ---\\ne3b0c442  \\nf5be287d  ## V2 (compaction) — Compaction summary quality (3-axis hand-rate)\\ne3b0c442  \\n17cf0f4c  **Fixture:** 10 multi-turn coding sessions with organic compaction. These can be\\ncccec9ee  the V8 session + 9 others (ideally: 3 each across qwen3.6-35b-a3b/v3.1,\\n0a0bebc7  qwen3.6-27b/v1.1, and gemma-4-26b-a4b-it/v2; the dense Gemma 31B is single-digit\\nb39cdba8  tok/s and may not produce enough turns to organically compact within a sitting —\\n6730cca6  exclude it from V2 unless an extended run is feasible).\\ne3b0c442  \\n84fbd316  **Protocol:**\\n1314f36d  1. Run 10 multi-turn sessions, each long enough that `shouldCompact()` triggers\\n9afc243c     at least once (≥ 75% of `max_input_tokens` = 114688 → ~86K tokens)\\n18e4debe  2. For each compaction, fetch the summary:\\nad332335  ```bash\\ne31a621d  cat ~/.emmy/telemetry/*.jsonl | \\\\\\n41f2ed44    jq 'select(.event==\\\"session.compaction.complete\\\") | {ts, profile, summary_tokens, summary}' \\\\\\nb8ac3efc    > /tmp/v2-compaction-summaries.json\\nf1b90184  ```\\n08515f7b  3. Hand-rate each summary on three axes:\\nd41625f2     - **Goal preservation** (≥ 80% target): does the summary preserve every\\n366c8307       explicit goal raised in the elided turns?\\ne4a1111f     - **Decision preservation** (≥ 70%): does it preserve decisions made?\\nb536a913       (e.g., \\\"we chose library X over Y because Z\\\")\\nbcc68d36     - **Error preservation** (100% — CRITICAL): does it preserve every error\\nc780a1d4       encountered + how it was resolved?\\n86196307  4. Average across 10 sessions per axis\\ne3b0c442  \\n8bd88cae  **Pass:** goal ≥ 80%, decision ≥ 70%, error 100%\\nb0856a78  **Fail behavior:** which axis missed determines the prompt revision per\\n0e4ced08  CONTEXT.md calibration plan:\\ncbe971cb  - Goal miss → add \\\"explicit goals\\\" emphasis\\n93bb5069  - Decision miss → add \\\"decisions made and their rationale\\\"\\n72730370  - Error miss → add \\\"errors and their resolutions\\\" stronger phrasing\\ne3b0c442  \\n70ae57d7  The current v1 prompt ALREADY names all three; if any axis misses despite that,\\n59e8a286  the prompt may need sectioning (deferred per CONTEXT.md \\\"Compaction prompt\\n6092b9ae  sectioning\\\" — Pitfall #5 trap).\\ne3b0c442  \\n02ee81fd  **Resume signal:** `v2 compaction quality green: goal=<pct>% decision=<pct>%\\n94ef347a  error=<pct>%` OR FAIL markers per axis\\ne3b0c442  \\ncb3f91d5  ---\\ne3b0c442  \\naf31c28a  ## V8 (compaction) — 2-hour real-deal session + arch-aware prefix-cache hit rate\\ne3b0c442  \\ne2823059  **Fixture:** sustained coding work on Qwen 3.6 35B-A3B v3.1 for ~2 hours.\\ne3b0c442  \\n84fbd316  **Protocol:**\\nf044b861  1. `pi-emmy --profile profiles/qwen3.6-35b-a3b/v3.1` (fresh session)\\n469ea5b0  2. Drive sustained work for ~2 hours; let compaction trigger organically\\nde1c82a0  3. Continuously check vLLM `/metrics` for preemption / OOM:\\nad332335  ```bash\\n5a7a6e1f  curl -s http://127.0.0.1:8002/metrics | grep -E \\\"preempt|oom\\\"\\n4bd86638  # → preempted_total{...} 0, out_of_memory_total{...} 0 throughout\\nf1b90184  ```\\n25ce95ae  4. After at least one compaction has fired, read prefix-cache hit rate:\\nad332335  ```bash\\ndaf7f2fd  curl -s http://127.0.0.1:8002/metrics | grep prefix_cache\\nbeb529c8  # Compute: hits / (hits + misses) post-compaction\\nf1b90184  ```\\n5fc56840  5. **Architecture-aware gate (per Pitfall #22):**\\n405dd0fc     - Qwen 35B-A3B is **Mamba-hybrid** → \\\"measure-and-acknowledge\\\"; record the\\ne81ee744       hit rate, do NOT fail-gate (vLLM marks Mamba prefix caching experimental\\n175209cd       and silently no-ops)\\nf41c73ad     - For attention-only profiles (qwen3.6-27b dense, gemma-4-31b-it dense),\\nc9eb8308       the same protocol with Qwen 27B as substrate → **hard ≥ 80%** post-compaction\\nb4f4bc2b  6. **Pass criteria for Mamba-hybrid path:**\\ne887b46d     - 0 preemptions across the 2-hour run\\n4ded902a     - 0 OOM kills\\na8d8a166     - At least one compaction fired and produced a non-empty summary\\n8ff6b31f     - Prefix-cache hit rate recorded (any value — informational only per Pitfall #22)\\nb19f48b0  7. **Pass criteria for attention-only path (optional V8' on Qwen 27B):**\\ned022e2c     - All Mamba-hybrid criteria above\\n5488b85d     - Plus prefix-cache hit rate ≥ 80% post-compaction\\ne3b0c442  \\n0ea83bdb  **Resume signal (Mamba-hybrid):** `v8 compaction real-deal green: 0 preempt/oom,\\n23d55962  hit_rate=<pct>% (mamba-hybrid measure-and-acknowledge)` OR FAIL with cause\\ne3b0c442  \\ndf951572  **Resume signal (attention-only optional):** `v8 compaction real-deal green\\n2a7ce91e  (attention-only): hit_rate=<pct>% ≥ 0.80`\\ne3b0c442  \\ncb3f91d5  ---\\ne3b0c442  \\n63d5bbc8  ## STATE.md acceptance ledger\\ne3b0c442  \\nb98b0965  When all 6 resume signals land, the planner flips the corresponding ledger\\n04333db5  entries from Done† → Done in `.planning/STATE.md`:\\ne3b0c442  \\na254e786  - Memory V1 (adoption) → Done\\n89f486a3  - Memory V2 (write discipline) → Done\\na05f99f6  - Memory V3 (rot protection — CRITICAL) → Done\\n2d7274e6  - Memory V8 (real-deal session) → Done\\nc533dde1  - Compaction V2 (summary quality) → Done\\nfa7046f4  - Compaction V8 (real-deal session + arch-aware cache hit) → Done\\ne3b0c442  \\n7138cb64  If any FAIL signals land, the corresponding plan re-engages in a follow-up\\n677bd7b0  revision pass:\\nf86f606e  - V1/V2/V8 (memory) FAIL → revise plan 04.4-01 description\\necb79751  - V3 (memory) FAIL → CRITICAL — revise description AND consider deferring\\ncb6e9878    v0.1 ship until re-run lands green\\nb39958d9  - V2/V8 (compaction) FAIL → revise plan 04.4-07 prompt\\ne3b0c442  \\ncb3f91d5  ---\\ne3b0c442  \\n884a90ca  ## Notes on running the protocols\\ne3b0c442  \\n149d198b  - All 6 protocols are inherently measurement-driven. They cannot run inside the\\nf3685530    executor wave. The wave-4 plan (04.4-09) lands this runbook + a STATE.md\\n53cf85db    closeout-pending stamp; the operator runs the protocols and types resume\\n7bc1c104    signals; the planner re-engages to flip the ledger and close the phase.\\nf04ea0a7  - **Operator time estimate:** ~2 hours total (V1 batch ~30 min, V2/V3\\n5c2c83b8    hand-rating ~30 min, V8 memory + V2 compaction can ride the same session,\\nb54e295d    V8 compaction = 2 hr standalone).\\n41da0fcf  - **Run order:** V1 first (produces V2 fixture), V3 second (independent), V8\\nd6693f93    memory + V2 compaction together (single 1-hour session), V8 compaction last\\nbb428271    (2-hour standalone, can overlap with daily-driver use).\\n\",\"line_count\":257}"}],"details":{"path":"/data/projects/emmy/.planning/phases/04.4-filesystem-memory-tool-append-only-prefix-compaction-polish-/04.4-09-OPERATOR-PROTOCOLS.md","binary":false,"lines":"b694c3de  # Phase 04.4 Closeout — Operator Verification Protocols\ne3b0c442  \n51733fc8  Six gates that require human-driven measurement; cannot run inside the executor wave.\ne4f085d8  Source of truth: MEMORY-TOOL-SPEC.md §10 + COMPACTION-DESIGN.md §8.\ne3b0c442  \nc15c7889  **Pre-conditions:**\n51d4a098  - Plans 04.4-01 through 04.4-08 landed (verified by their SUMMARY.md files)\na27a5040  - 4 shipped profile bundles warm-bootable (qwen3.6-35b-a3b/v3.1, qwen3.6-27b/v1.1, gemma-4-26b-a4b-it/v2, gemma-4-31b-it/v1.1)\n2a098144  - Telemetry sinks alive (`~/.emmy/telemetry/*.jsonl` + Langfuse loopback)\n09da1e0f  - vLLM `/metrics` reachable on loopback for V8 prefix-cache hit-rate read\ne3b0c442  \ncb3f91d5  ---\ne3b0c442  \n81e42614  ## V1 — Memory adoption ≥ 60% (Qwen 35B-A3B v3.1)\ne3b0c442  \n32a4a000  **Fixture:** 20-task batch — pick tasks that present a \"would benefit from a note\"\n9ce48c2c  moment. Examples:\nf559a824  - \"Find and fix the off-by-one bug in `src/parsers/tokenizer.ts`\"\nfb642452  - \"Add a new endpoint following the existing CRUD convention\"\n7c6065c6  - \"What was that hashline edit pattern again?\"\ne68975d8  - \"We had to use TextEncoder for prefix-hash bytes — explain why\"\ne3b0c442  \n7db3fbb9  Each task is a fresh session; memory tool enabled (default); project + global scope\n8993f73f  clean before task 1, then accumulating.\ne3b0c442  \n84fbd316  **Protocol:**\nc4d44de2  1. `pi-emmy --profile profiles/qwen3.6-35b-a3b/v3.1` (no `--no-memory`)\n1517afd3  2. Run all 20 tasks; record each session's transcript via JSONL telemetry\n7020743f  3. For each task, hand-rate:\n246002c6     - Did the model `view /memories/...` before the work? (Y/N)\nfc4a94af     - Did it write a note via `create` or `str_replace` when a discovery was made? (Y/N — only when applicable)\n6e4bedb5  4. Adoption = (sessions with at least one `view` call) / 20\n42362f1f  5. **Pass:** adoption ≥ 60%\n90b2fbc5  6. **Fail behavior:** revise tool description in plan 04.4-01 per CONTEXT.md\ne51a6812     \"Calibration protocol: measurement-driven expansion only\"; re-run.\ne3b0c442  \ne68b47eb  **Resume signal:** `v1 memory adoption green: <observed_pct>%` OR\nad0a1a7b  `v1 memory adoption FAIL — observed <pct>%, recommend description revision`\ne3b0c442  \ncb3f91d5  ---\ne3b0c442  \nf02f91be  ## V2 (memory) — Memory write discipline ≥ 70% load-bearing\ne3b0c442  \n2b953eb2  **Fixture:** every `create` and `str_replace` op in the V1 run's JSONL telemetry.\na86b3deb  Reuses the V1 sessions; no new run needed.\ne3b0c442  \n84fbd316  **Protocol:**\nad332335  ```bash\ne31a621d  cat ~/.emmy/telemetry/*.jsonl | \\\n21e67919    jq 'select(.event==\"memory.op\" and (.[\"emmy.memory.command\"]==\"create\" or .[\"emmy.memory.command\"]==\"str_replace\"))' \\\nb3effd16    > /tmp/v2-write-ops.json\nf1b90184  ```\ne3b0c442  \n7c422217  For each write: hand-rate **load-bearing** vs **narrative**:\nb055479a  - **YES (load-bearing):** API quirk, project convention, hard-won discovery,\n2e9c91a3    counter-intuitive finding, dead-end others should skip\nee07f92e  - **NO (narrative):** \"then I fixed the bug\", already-obvious facts, transient state\ne3b0c442  \ndb524cfa  Discipline = (load-bearing writes) / (total writes)\ne3b0c442  \n4d3b45ec  **Pass:** discipline ≥ 70%\na63c5ca4  **Fail behavior:** description didn't sufficiently discourage narrative; expand\n410ffaa4  description with sterner phrasing per CONTEXT.md calibration protocol.\ne3b0c442  \n43f408ac  **Resume signal:** `v2 memory discipline green: <observed_pct>%` OR\ne9349029  `v2 memory discipline FAIL — observed <pct>%, narrative writes: <samples>`\ne3b0c442  \ncb3f91d5  ---\ne3b0c442  \n7ea39973  ## V3 — Memory rot protection 100% — CRITICAL DIMENSION\ne3b0c442  \n23d57f9b  **Fixture:** 5 planted contradicting notes pre-loaded into a fresh test project's\nd1991a1c  `/memories/project/`. The 5 plants are designed so each is checkable against a\nc6bf8e36  specific code file in the test fixture project:\ne3b0c442  \n3c0cd583  1. `notes/api-format.md`: \"Always use `requestId` in JSON payloads (camelCase)\" —\n09732047     but the code actually uses `request_id` (snake_case)\n52c2088a  2. `notes/auth.md`: \"Tokens are signed with HS256\" — but `auth.ts` actually uses RS256\na4e204e1  3. `notes/db-pool.md`: \"Database max connections is 50\" — actual config says 200\n75e0aac8  4. `notes/env-var.md`: \"Set `LOG_LEVEL=verbose` to enable debug\" — actual code reads `DEBUG=1`\n5e75a626  5. `notes/route.md`: \"POST /api/v1/users for create\" — actual route is `POST /users`\n1c991f84     (no /api/v1)\ne3b0c442  \n84fbd316  **Protocol:**\na914e707  1. Set up the planted notes in a fresh test project under `/tmp/v3-rot-test/`\n68faeea0     with corresponding source files containing the truth\n2b73ca26  2. `cd /tmp/v3-rot-test && pi-emmy --profile profiles/qwen3.6-35b-a3b/v3.1`\n23309f62  3. Ask each of the 5 questions in a fresh session (or one session — both valid):\n13a03817     - \"What's the JSON field convention here? Should I use camelCase or snake_case?\"\n39b26ace     - \"What signing algorithm does `auth.ts` use?\"\n693dfc07     - \"What's the max database connections this app uses?\"\ncf4dd0c3     - \"How do I enable debug logging?\"\n77624f22     - \"What's the user-creation endpoint path?\"\n900714ea  4. For each, observe: did the model TRUST the note blindly, or did it CHECK the\n6edaba03     code (read source file) before answering?\n979989b5  5. **Pass:** 5/5 — model checked code AND surfaced the contradiction OR followed\nfe83d49e     the code-truth answer\n86c739c7  6. **Fail behavior:** rot protection is the CRITICAL DIMENSION. If <5/5, the tool\nb451946d     description needs sterner \"verify before trusting\" language; consider adding\n879e769c     `last_updated:` line to note metadata (deferred per CONTEXT.md Claude's discretion).\ne3b0c442  \n0c353d73  **Resume signal:** `v3 memory rot green: 5/5` OR\n6ee55445  `v3 memory rot FAIL — <N>/5, samples where model trusted note: <list>`\ne3b0c442  \ncb3f91d5  ---\ne3b0c442  \nf18d9a90  ## V8 (memory) — 1-hour real-deal live session\ne3b0c442  \n7cb74cc6  **Fixture:** any non-trivial coding task that takes ~1 hour with the agent.\n1889f033  Examples:\n521048f2  - \"Add an OAuth2 PKCE flow to the sample app + tests\"\n23f7170c  - \"Refactor the parser module to support streaming\"\n69f94328  - \"Build a Phase 5 dashboard component end-to-end\"\ne3b0c442  \n92ffc9b7  Operator chooses one.\ne3b0c442  \n84fbd316  **Protocol:**\na86ef3fe  1. `pi-emmy --profile profiles/qwen3.6-35b-a3b/v3.1` (default profile, fresh session)\n53fda6a4  2. Drive the agent through the task for ~60 minutes\nf7bf9c6e  3. Observe organically:\n0794ea64     - 1–5 memory notes created across the session (not 0, not 20)\n275fc47e     - No narrative writes (\"then I added the import\")\n0b832d0b     - No quota errors in JSONL: `grep memory.quota_exceeded ~/.emmy/telemetry/*.jsonl`\nfb3891fb     - No rot incidents (model didn't trust a stale note over fresh code)\nd25e742c     - All write ops have `emmy.memory.scope` and load-bearing reasoning\nac58cf35  4. **Pass:** all 5 sub-criteria green\nd7171324  5. **Fail behavior:** record which sub-criterion failed; specific revision path\nb18f84d7     depends on the failure (typically loops back to V1/V2/V3 fixes)\ne3b0c442  \nb1a028bc  Quick post-session checks:\nad332335  ```bash\n1235192a  grep -E 'memory.quota_exceeded' ~/.emmy/telemetry/*.jsonl   # → 0 matches\ne31a621d  cat ~/.emmy/telemetry/*.jsonl | \\\n9c66b696    jq 'select(.event==\"memory.op\" and .[\"emmy.memory.command\"]==\"create\")' | \\\n9c295a94    jq -s 'length'                                            # → 1..5\nf1b90184  ```\ne3b0c442  \n96e1e442  **Resume signal:** `v8 memory real-deal green` (counts: <N notes>; quota errors: 0;\nee69d974  rot incidents: 0) OR FAIL markers per failed sub-criterion\ne3b0c442  \ncb3f91d5  ---\ne3b0c442  \nf5be287d  ## V2 (compaction) — Compaction summary quality (3-axis hand-rate)\ne3b0c442  \n17cf0f4c  **Fixture:** 10 multi-turn coding sessions with organic compaction. These can be\ncccec9ee  the V8 session + 9 others (ideally: 3 each across qwen3.6-35b-a3b/v3.1,\n0a0bebc7  qwen3.6-27b/v1.1, and gemma-4-26b-a4b-it/v2; the dense Gemma 31B is single-digit\nb39cdba8  tok/s and may not produce enough turns to organically compact within a sitting —\n6730cca6  exclude it from V2 unless an extended run is feasible).\ne3b0c442  \n84fbd316  **Protocol:**\n1314f36d  1. Run 10 multi-turn sessions, each long enough that `shouldCompact()` triggers\n9afc243c     at least once (≥ 75% of `max_input_tokens` = 114688 → ~86K tokens)\n18e4debe  2. For each compaction, fetch the summary:\nad332335  ```bash\ne31a621d  cat ~/.emmy/telemetry/*.jsonl | \\\n41f2ed44    jq 'select(.event==\"session.compaction.complete\") | {ts, profile, summary_tokens, summary}' \\\nb8ac3efc    > /tmp/v2-compaction-summaries.json\nf1b90184  ```\n08515f7b  3. Hand-rate each summary on three axes:\nd41625f2     - **Goal preservation** (≥ 80% target): does the summary preserve every\n366c8307       explicit goal raised in the elided turns?\ne4a1111f     - **Decision preservation** (≥ 70%): does it preserve decisions made?\nb536a913       (e.g., \"we chose library X over Y because Z\")\nbcc68d36     - **Error preservation** (100% — CRITICAL): does it preserve every error\nc780a1d4       encountered + how it was resolved?\n86196307  4. Average across 10 sessions per axis\ne3b0c442  \n8bd88cae  **Pass:** goal ≥ 80%, decision ≥ 70%, error 100%\nb0856a78  **Fail behavior:** which axis missed determines the prompt revision per\n0e4ced08  CONTEXT.md calibration plan:\ncbe971cb  - Goal miss → add \"explicit goals\" emphasis\n93bb5069  - Decision miss → add \"decisions made and their rationale\"\n72730370  - Error miss → add \"errors and their resolutions\" stronger phrasing\ne3b0c442  \n70ae57d7  The current v1 prompt ALREADY names all three; if any axis misses despite that,\n59e8a286  the prompt may need sectioning (deferred per CONTEXT.md \"Compaction prompt\n6092b9ae  sectioning\" — Pitfall #5 trap).\ne3b0c442  \n02ee81fd  **Resume signal:** `v2 compaction quality green: goal=<pct>% decision=<pct>%\n94ef347a  error=<pct>%` OR FAIL markers per axis\ne3b0c442  \ncb3f91d5  ---\ne3b0c442  \naf31c28a  ## V8 (compaction) — 2-hour real-deal session + arch-aware prefix-cache hit rate\ne3b0c442  \ne2823059  **Fixture:** sustained coding work on Qwen 3.6 35B-A3B v3.1 for ~2 hours.\ne3b0c442  \n84fbd316  **Protocol:**\nf044b861  1. `pi-emmy --profile profiles/qwen3.6-35b-a3b/v3.1` (fresh session)\n469ea5b0  2. Drive sustained work for ~2 hours; let compaction trigger organically\nde1c82a0  3. Continuously check vLLM `/metrics` for preemption / OOM:\nad332335  ```bash\n5a7a6e1f  curl -s http://127.0.0.1:8002/metrics | grep -E \"preempt|oom\"\n4bd86638  # → preempted_total{...} 0, out_of_memory_total{...} 0 throughout\nf1b90184  ```\n25ce95ae  4. After at least one compaction has fired, read prefix-cache hit rate:\nad332335  ```bash\ndaf7f2fd  curl -s http://127.0.0.1:8002/metrics | grep prefix_cache\nbeb529c8  # Compute: hits / (hits + misses) post-compaction\nf1b90184  ```\n5fc56840  5. **Architecture-aware gate (per Pitfall #22):**\n405dd0fc     - Qwen 35B-A3B is **Mamba-hybrid** → \"measure-and-acknowledge\"; record the\ne81ee744       hit rate, do NOT fail-gate (vLLM marks Mamba prefix caching experimental\n175209cd       and silently no-ops)\nf41c73ad     - For attention-only profiles (qwen3.6-27b dense, gemma-4-31b-it dense),\nc9eb8308       the same protocol with Qwen 27B as substrate → **hard ≥ 80%** post-compaction\nb4f4bc2b  6. **Pass criteria for Mamba-hybrid path:**\ne887b46d     - 0 preemptions across the 2-hour run\n4ded902a     - 0 OOM kills\na8d8a166     - At least one compaction fired and produced a non-empty summary\n8ff6b31f     - Prefix-cache hit rate recorded (any value — informational only per Pitfall #22)\nb19f48b0  7. **Pass criteria for attention-only path (optional V8' on Qwen 27B):**\ned022e2c     - All Mamba-hybrid criteria above\n5488b85d     - Plus prefix-cache hit rate ≥ 80% post-compaction\ne3b0c442  \n0ea83bdb  **Resume signal (Mamba-hybrid):** `v8 compaction real-deal green: 0 preempt/oom,\n23d55962  hit_rate=<pct>% (mamba-hybrid measure-and-acknowledge)` OR FAIL with cause\ne3b0c442  \ndf951572  **Resume signal (attention-only optional):** `v8 compaction real-deal green\n2a7ce91e  (attention-only): hit_rate=<pct>% ≥ 0.80`\ne3b0c442  \ncb3f91d5  ---\ne3b0c442  \n63d5bbc8  ## STATE.md acceptance ledger\ne3b0c442  \nb98b0965  When all 6 resume signals land, the planner flips the corresponding ledger\n04333db5  entries from Done† → Done in `.planning/STATE.md`:\ne3b0c442  \na254e786  - Memory V1 (adoption) → Done\n89f486a3  - Memory V2 (write discipline) → Done\na05f99f6  - Memory V3 (rot protection — CRITICAL) → Done\n2d7274e6  - Memory V8 (real-deal session) → Done\nc533dde1  - Compaction V2 (summary quality) → Done\nfa7046f4  - Compaction V8 (real-deal session + arch-aware cache hit) → Done\ne3b0c442  \n7138cb64  If any FAIL signals land, the corresponding plan re-engages in a follow-up\n677bd7b0  revision pass:\nf86f606e  - V1/V2/V8 (memory) FAIL → revise plan 04.4-01 description\necb79751  - V3 (memory) FAIL → CRITICAL — revise description AND consider deferring\ncb6e9878    v0.1 ship until re-run lands green\nb39958d9  - V2/V8 (compaction) FAIL → revise plan 04.4-07 prompt\ne3b0c442  \ncb3f91d5  ---\ne3b0c442  \n884a90ca  ## Notes on running the protocols\ne3b0c442  \n149d198b  - All 6 protocols are inherently measurement-driven. They cannot run inside the\nf3685530    executor wave. The wave-4 plan (04.4-09) lands this runbook + a STATE.md\n53cf85db    closeout-pending stamp; the operator runs the protocols and types resume\n7bc1c104    signals; the planner re-engages to flip the ledger and close the phase.\nf04ea0a7  - **Operator time estimate:** ~2 hours total (V1 batch ~30 min, V2/V3\n5c2c83b8    hand-rating ~30 min, V8 memory + V2 compaction can ride the same session,\nb54e295d    V8 compaction = 2 hr standalone).\n41da0fcf  - **Run order:** V1 first (produces V2 fixture), V3 second (independent), V8\nd6693f93    memory + V2 compaction together (single 1-hour session), V8 compaction last\nbb428271    (2-hour standalone, can overlap with daily-driver use).\n","line_count":257},"isError":false,"timestamp":1777254885690}],"profile":{"id":"qwen3.6-35b-a3b","version":"v3.1","hash":"sha256:4da61fd4eec31ba079204ce43119ff39ced0ae0f1989037cc2a68c5a89c272ba","path":"/data/projects/emmy/profiles/qwen3.6-35b-a3b/v3.1"}}
